No voice but Albert's gains her pensive ear — No
hastes impatient to the waving shade
Fortune to him her gifts did never impart : But kinder Nature gave the loveliest frame , And gave ( much more ) the most unblemished heart
While in soft converse passed the livelong day
no time their passion should allay
rich clouds of gold and purple hue
the bower , Whose shade encircled all her soul held dear

their vows of endless love : Unhappy pair ! your passion is betrayed — Fatal to both those vows must shortly prove : For , as it chanced , in that ill-fated hour Near the green arbour Anselm musing passed ; Heard their discourse , and , entering in the bower , The trembling lovers sunk confused , aghast
Who thus canst stoop to this ignoble choice
" Parental fondness from this injured heart

the detested object you desire — — " Thy loved Cecilia shall be ever thine , " If to the summit of yonder verdant hill , " Whose lofty brow overlooks this ample plain , " You bear the maid ; nor rest a moment , till " Even to the top thy venturous steps attain . "
The object of its fond pursuits
of gladness on each face appear When love still strives where human efforts fail
that with discordant sound Whispered remorse to Anselm's wounded ear : He felt their force ; he heaved a sigh profound , And pitying dropped too late a fruitless tear
It's past , Cecilia ! soon approaching Death

of all my grief and joy
let my image from thy thought depart

Angels of death around his spirit
her balmy lips no more are red
her icy breast no longer beat
the sacred grave , Which still of the Two Lovers bears the name
